#: ../../S/superprogrammer.rst:5
msgid "superprogrammer"
msgstr "superprogrammer"

#: ../../S/superprogrammer.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../S/superprogrammer.rst:9
msgid ""
"A prolific programmer; one who can code exceedingly well and quickly. Not "
"all hackers are superprogrammers, but many are. (Productivity can vary from "
"one programmer to another by three orders of magnitude. For example, one "
"programmer might be able to write an average of 3 lines of working code in "
"one day, while another, with the proper tools, might be able to write 3,000."
" This range is astonishing; it is matched in very few other areas of human "
"endeavor.) The term superprogrammer is more commonly used within such places"
" as IBM than in the hacker community. It tends to stress naive measures of "
"productivity and to underweight creativity, ingenuity, and getting the job "
"*done* — and to sidestep the question of whether the 3,000 lines of code do "
"more or less useful work than three lines that do the :ref:`Right-Thing`\\. "
"Hackers tend to prefer the terms :ref:`hacker` and :ref:`wizard`\\."
msgstr ""
"多作な "
"programmer。並外れてうまく、速くコーディングできる者。すべてのハッカーがsuperprogrammerなわけではないが、多くがそうだ。(生産性は、ある"
" programmer から別の programmer へ、3桁も変わりうる。たとえば、ある programmer "
"は1日に平均3行の動くコードを書けるかもしれないが、別の者は、適切なツールがあれば3000行書けるかもしれない。この幅は驚異的で、人間の営みの他の分野ではほとんど例を見ない。)superprogrammerという用語は、ハッカーのコミュニティよりも、IBMのような場所でより一般的に使われる。それは生産性の素朴な尺度を強調し、創造性、独創性、仕事を片付けることを過小評価しがちで——3000行のコードが、\\"
" :ref:`Right-Thing`\\ を行う3行より多くの、あるいは少ない有用な仕事をするのかという問いを避ける傾向がある。ハッカーは\\ "
":ref:`hacker`\\ や\\ :ref:`wizard`\\ という用語を好む傾向がある。"
